      "\n<li>Maple Cafe is open just in time for Spring!</li>\n<li>Cassandra wants you to help out at the cafe as a manager. Are you up for the task?</li>\n<li>Accept ‘[Maple Cafe on a Spring Day] Hitting the Ground Running’ quest within the star event notifier on the left side of the screen.</li>\n<li>After completing the tutorial quest, you will gain access to the exclusive UI via ‘[Maple Cafe on a Spring Day] Entering the Cafe’ quest within the star event notifier.</li>\n<li>There are a total of 8 baristas and each has different missions that require your help.</li>\n<li>You can help up to 3 baristas at the same time. Feel free to change the selected baristas by clicking on them again on the UI.</li>\n<li>Once you complete the missions, you will receive Chat Points for the barista whose mission you’ve completed.</li>\n<li>Each barista’s mission has a different daily activation limit depending on the amount of Chat Points given per completion.<br>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Cayne:</strong> 20 times</li>\n<li><strong>Kenshin:</strong> 8 times</li>\n<li><strong>Shingen:</strong> 10 times</li>\n<li><strong>Alika:</strong> 8 times</li>\n<li><strong>Gillie:</strong> 8 times</li>\n<li><strong>Haruaki:</strong> 6 times</li>\n<li><strong>Becky:</strong> 5 times</li>\n<li><strong>Dr. Jang:</strong> 5 times</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>You can collect up to 500 Chat Points per barista per day. In total, you can have up to 4,000 Chat Points a day.</li>\n<li>Your Rapport with a specific barista will level up based on the cumulative Chat Points you’ve accumulated with that barista. You can build up to Rapport 15 with each of the baristas.<br>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Rapport 1:</strong> 400 Chat Points</li>\n<li><strong>Rapport 2:</strong> 400 Chat Points</li>\n<li><strong>Rapport 3:</strong> 500 Chat Points</li>\n<li><strong>Rapport 4:</strong> 500 Chat Points</li>\n<li><strong>Rapport 5:</strong> 500 Chat Points</li>\n<li><strong>Rapport 6:</strong> 600 Chat Points</li>\n<li><strong>Rapport 7:</strong> 600 Chat Points</li>\n<li><strong>Rapport 8:</strong> 700 Chat Points</li>\n<li><strong>Rapport 9:</strong> 700 Chat Points</li>\n<li><strong>Rapport 10:</strong> 700 Chat Points</li>\n<li><strong>Rapport 11:</strong> 800 Chat Points</li>\n<li><strong>Rapport 12:</strong> 900 Chat Points</li>\n<li><strong>Rapport 13:</strong> 900 Chat Points</li>\n<li><strong>Rapport 14:</strong> 900 Chat Points</li>\n<li><strong>Rapport 15:</strong> 1,000 Chat Points</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Pit-a-Pat Pass</strong><br>\n<ul>\n<li>Pit-a-Pat Pass holders will receive additional perks and rewards!</li>\n<li>The additional perks are the following:<br>\n<ul>\n<li>Increased daily chat point capacity by 50%</li>\n<li>Increased chat points received upon mission completion by 50%</li>\n<li>Access to exclusive rewards</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>You can purchase <strong>Pit-a-Pat Package</strong> either from the Cash Shop or the event UI to obtain a <strong>Pit-a-Pat Pass Coupon</strong> as well as <strong>My Beating Heart Hat</strong>, <strong>My Beating Heart Cape</strong>, and <strong>My Beating Heart Outfit</strong> (Cash items can be transferred to the Cash Shop Inventory. ).</li>\n<li>Pit-a-Pat Pass can be purchased and applied per character.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Rewards will unlock for every 5 cumulative Rapports.</li>\n<li>Maple Cafe on a Spring Day event can be done per character.</li>\n",
